                <p className="text-xs text-[#E8E9E4]/70 leading-relaxed">User screenshot showed ~400px of empty space between Quality Gate and the ENTERED UP/DOWN buttons on the mobile signal tab. Cause: <code className="text-[10px] bg-[#0E100F] px-1">mt-auto</code> on the &ldquo;-30% Stop Guard Sync&rdquo; block was pushing it to the bottom of a viewport-tall flex column. The intent (from a much earlier version) was filling desktop empty space; mobile got dead patches instead. Replaced with <code className="text-[10px] bg-[#0E100F] px-1">mt-4</code>. Buttons now sit naturally below Quality Gate with normal spacing on every screen size.</p>
